Powershell script for non compliant devices 



Step by step guide on how to implement this script
==================================================
Press Windows Key + R on your keyboard
Type powershell and press Enter
Right-click on PowerShell and select "Run as administrator"
Click "Yes" when prompted by User Account Control

In PowerShell, navigate to where you want to save the script (or use the default location):
Example "cd C:\Users\YourUsername\Documents" (Replace YourUsername with your actual Windows username)

Create a new PowerShell script file
"notepad Get-NonCompliantDevices.ps1"

Copy the entire script
Paste it into the Notepad window (Ctrl + V)
Click File → Save (or Ctrl + S)
Close Notepad

Back in PowerShell, run this command to allow script execution: "Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser"
Type Y and press Enter when prompted
Wait for the command to complete

In PowerShell, run the script: ".\Get-NonCompliantDevices.ps1"

A browser window will automatically open
Sign in with your Azure/Microsoft 365 admin account
You'll see a permissions request - click "Accept" or "Consent"
After successful authentication, return to PowerShell
The script will begin fetching devices

The script will display output like this: 
Found 3 non-compliant device(s):

Device Name: LAPTOP-ABC123 | User: john.doe@company.com
Device Name: DESKTOP-XYZ789 | User: jane.smith@company.com



Current requirements on system to be able to run the script
===========================================================
"Requires Intune Administrator role minimum" 



What this script will do
========================
Create a report that shows the device name and the user who has a non compliant device


If you want to run this script on a schedule (e.g., daily), you can create a Windows Task Scheduler job:
========================================================================================================
Open Task Scheduler (search for it in Windows)
Click Create Basic Task
Name it: Intune Compliance Check
Set the trigger (e.g., Daily at 9 AM)
Set the action to: C:\Windows\System32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\powershell.exe
Add arguments: -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "C:\Users\YourUsername\Documents\Get-NonCompliantDevices.ps1"
